Questions:
What alternative options are available to you if you choose not to participate in the Community Support Program for Lung Cancer Screening study?
A) You will be provided with a private car service for your medical appointments;
B) You will still have your scheduled lung cancer screening appointment without the additional support from the study;
C) You will receive a personal health coach to assist with your healthcare needs;
D) You will be enrolled in a different study focused on lung health improvement.

Correct answer: B

How will the University of Pennsylvania protect your personal information during the study?
A) By publishing your name and personal information for research transparency;
B) By using password-protected computer files and limiting access to study staff;
C) By sharing all your personal information with the public;
D) By not collecting any personal information at all.

Correct answer: B

If you have questions about your rights as a research participant or wish to discuss problems or concerns related to the study, whom should you contact?

A) The Institutional Review Board (IRB) at the University of Pennsylvania;
B) The Principal Investigator (PI) of the study;
C) The local health department;
D) Your personal healthcare provider.

Correct answer: A) The Institutional Review Board (IRB) at the University of Pennsylvania;
